{"parentUuid":"7ae882c4-7f6c-47e4-ac6d-d5158053bf75","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01D3soXNeLx3Mv3KTaPY3vX8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"DuckDB has **no shell-quoting helper**. Here's what I found:\n\n**No matches** for `ShellQuote`/`ShellEscape`/`QuoteShell`/`EscapeShell`/`QuoteArg`/`EscapeArg` anywhere in the tree.\n\n**`StringUtil` has no shell helper** — only `SplitWithQuote` at `duckdb/src/include/duckdb/common/string_util.hpp:154` (the inverse direction — splitting CSV-style quoted input).\n\n**`popen()` is used inside DuckDB**, but only in `duckdb/tools/shell/shell.cpp` (the interactive CLI), and the inputs there are passed straight through (`pager_command.c_str()` line 1429, `zFile.c_str() + 1` line 2006) — they're not sanitized because the CLI user is explicitly opting in to a shell. So nothing to crib from.\n\n**Other `Escape`/`Sanitize` functions exist** but are domain-specific and not shell-safe: `KeywordHelper::EscapeQuotes`/`WriteQuoted` (SQL identifiers/literals), `StringUtil::SQLIdentifierLiteral`, `LikeMatcher`/regex escapes, CSV-value escaping. None of these handle `$`, backticks, `\\`, `;`, `|`, `&`, newlines, etc. the way a shell needs.\n\n**Recommendation:** rather than quoting for `popen`, prefer `posix_spawn` (or `fork` + `execvp`) with an `argv` array — no shell, no quoting problem, no injection surface. DuckDB itself doesn't avoid this because its only `popen` call sites are *intended* to run shell.\n\nIf you must use `popen`, the POSIX-safe rule is: wrap the arg in single quotes and replace every embedded `'` with `'\\''`. That covers everything except a literal NUL byte (which `popen` can't carry anyway). You'd need to write that helper yourself — there isn't one to reuse."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1828,"cache_read_input_tokens":27800,"output_tokens":966,"server_to